text: Peter Bryden Malinauskas (born 14 August 1980) is a South Australian politician. He has served as the Premier of South Australia since 2022, as leader of the South Australian Labor Party since 2018 and as the member for Croydon since 2018. He is of Hungarian, Lithuanian and Irish descent. ==References== Category:1980 births Category:Living people Category:Premiers of South Australia Category:Australian Labor Party politicians
